Fixed the app freezing indefinitely (one CPU core at 100%) after a scan when clicking **Close & Load** with auto-select on. Auto-selecting + auto-previewing a tall portrait keeper triggered an unbounded resize⇄refit loop in the single-image preview: with the vertical scrollbar set to "as needed", the fitted image's height straddled the viewport and toggled the scrollbar on/off, each toggle resizing the viewport and forcing another refit. The single-image preview now reserves the vertical scrollbar so the viewport width stays constant and the fit converges.
